From: Thaison Nguyen <mail@thaison-nguyen.de>
Date: Wed, 23 Jul 2026 10:00:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] Port nv_kthread_q from UVM module to core nvidia module

Port NVIDIA's authoritative kthread-based workqueue (nv_kthread_q) from the
UVM module into the core nvidia module. This replaces the system
workqueue (schedule_work/flush_scheduled_work) with a module-owned kthread
FIFO executor, avoiding the Linux system-wide workqueue flush warning while
keeping nvidia-modeset out of scope.

The nv_kthread_q API is found in NVIDIA's UVM module and provides:
- A dedicated kthread that processes queued work items
- owned_allocation support for automatic memory cleanup
- Double-flush handling for self-rescheduling bottom halves

Key adaptations for the core module:
- Added owned_allocation field to nv_kthread_q_item for os_free_mem cleanup
- Used void * callback signature with cast at call site (Option B)
- Wrapped NVIDIA's init/stop in nv_kthread_core_q_init()/nv_kthread_core_q_shutdown()
- Integrated into module lifecycle (init before rm_init_rm, shutdown in error paths and exit)

Bug fixes applied during integration:
- Fixed NV_WORKQUEUE_SCHEDULE call sites to pass nv_work_t * (not nv_kthread_q_item_t *)
- Updated nv_gvi_kern_bh declaration to use nv_task_t *
- Added missing includes (nv.h, os-interface.h) in nv-kthread-q.c
- Used nv_vm_flags_set() wrapper for const vm_flags compatibility
- Commented out unsupported conftest remap_page_range in UVM Kbuild

This port enables the core module to defer work to a dedicated kthread,
which is a prerequisite for the modeset/DRM/UVM testing phase.

Signed-off-by: Thaison Nguyen <mail@thaison-nguyen.de>
---

